 <br>
Released February 18, 2003<br>
<br>
Henderson named AGFC director <br>
<br>
LITTLE ROCK - Commissioners from the Arkansas Game and Fish Commission today appointed Scott Henderson as the agency’s new director. Henderson replaces Hugh Durham who resigned on Monday.<br>
<br>
Henderson has worked for the AGFC since 1972. He is presently the agency’s assistant director and has been in that position since 1987.<br>
<br>
Commission chairman Jim Hinkle said the selection of Henderson was an easy task. “He’s a good fit for this organization. We didn’t have to travel far to find the best person for this job,” Hinkle said. Henderson takes over the reins of the 540-person agency today.<br>
<br>
Scott Henderson biographical information:<br>
<br>
Born in Newport, Ark. in 1948. <br>
1970 graduate of Arkansas State University with a Bachelor of Science degree in zoology. <br>
1970-72: Taught high school chemistry and biology in Melbourne, Fla. <br>
1972 - Began career with the AGFC as a fish truck driver at the Joe Hogan State Fish Hatchery in Lonoke. <br>
Has served as a fisheries research biologist, assistant chief of fisheries, chief of fisheries and was promoted in 1987 to assistant director. <br>
Married to the former Cathy Crow of Rector. They have two children: Mark and Karen. <br>
